release version 1.0

how to run XNAT_file_pipeline.py
1. #./XNAT_file_pipeline.py -id [PatientID]  
   for example:
   if input files are local:
   #./XNAT_file_pipeline.py -id CUPS003 -L
   #./XNAT_file_pipeline.py -id CUPS003 -L -v  (run in verbose mode)
   #./XNAT_file_pipeline.py -id CUPS003 -L -D  (run in debug mode)
   if input files are on the server [monted path]:
   #./XNAT_file_pipeline.py -id CUPS003
   #./XNAT_file_pipeline.py -id CUPS003 -v  (run in verbose mode)
   #./XNAT_file_pipeline.py -id CUPS003 -D  (run in debug mode)

2. run with batch of input files:
   cups
   for e in cups_ids:
       XNAT_file_pipeline.py -id $e
3. test dcm files:
   test_dcm.py [dcm_file]
4. script to view find dicom file with Weasis viewer:
   weasis.sh [dicom_file;
